&gt; &lt;kris@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; This is possible. You need to have a valid order.xml and then you
&gt; specify it
&gt; &gt; on the command line.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; The following is Heritrix&#39;s command line usage help:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; ---
&gt; &gt; Usage: heritrix --help
&gt; &gt; Usage: heritrix --nowui ORDER.XML
&gt; &gt; Usage: heritrix [--port=#] [--admin=LOGIN:PWRD] [--jmx[=#]] [--run]
&gt; &gt; [ORDER.XML]
&gt; &gt; Usage: heritrix [--port=#] --selftest[=TESTNAME]
&gt; &gt; Version: @VERSION@
&gt; &gt; Options:
&gt; &gt; -a,--admin Login and password for web user interface
&gt; administration.
&gt; &gt; Default: admin/letmein.
&gt; &gt; -h,--help Prints this message and exits.
&gt; &gt; -j,--jmx Start JMX. Allows remote control. Default jmxmp
&gt; port 8081.
&gt; &gt; -n,--nowui Put heritrix into run mode and begin crawl using
&gt; ORDER.XML.
&gt; &gt; Do
&gt; &gt; not put up web user interface.
&gt; &gt; -p,--port Port to run web user interface on. Default: 8080.
&gt; &gt; -r,--run Put heritrix into run mode. If ORDER.XML begin crawl.
&gt; &gt; -s,--selftest Run the integrated selftests. Pass test name to test it
&gt; &gt; only
&gt; &gt; (Case sensitive: E.g. pass &#39;Charset&#39; to run charset
&gt; &gt; selftest).
&gt; &gt; Arguments:
&gt; &gt; ORDER.XML Crawl order to run.
&gt; &gt; ---
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; So something along the lines of:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; heritrix --nowui /myjob/order.xml
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; should do the trick.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; If you don&#39;t specify the --nowui (which eliminates the web UI) you
&gt; need to
&gt; &gt; specify --run, or else the job will be held pending, until an operator
&gt; &gt; starts it via the WUI.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; - Kris
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; P.s. I&#39;m sure many on the list would be interested in knowning to which
&gt; &gt; purpose you are putting Heritrix, if you don&#39;t mind sharing.
